==English==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/frɛt/}}

===Etymology 1===
Old English [[fretan]], from a base corresponding to [[for-]] + [[eat]].  Cognate with Dutch [[vreten]], German [[fressen]].

====Verb====
{{en-verb|fret|t|ing}}

# ''(transitive, obsolete)'' to [[devour]], [[consume]]
# ''(transitive and intransitive)'' To [[gnaw]], [[consume]], eat away.
# ''(transitive)'' To [[chafe]] or [[irritate]]; to [[worry]].
# ''(intransitive)'' To [[worry]] or be [[anxious]].

===Etymology 2===
Origin unknown.

====Noun====
{{en-noun-reg}}
# One of the pieces of metal/wood/plastic across the neck of a [[guitar]] or other musical instrument that marks note positions for fingering.

# An ornamental pattern consisting of repeated vertical and horizonal lines (often in relief).


